3ï¸âƒ£ How does Devise store passwords?
âœ… Short answer

Devise uses bcrypt to store encrypted passwords in the encrypted_password column.

ğŸ” Deep explanation

Plain passwords are never stored

Uses one-way hashing

BCrypt::Password.create(password)

Compared during login, never decrypted

4ï¸âƒ£ Where does Devise store logged-in user information?
âœ… Short answer

Devise stores the user ID in the session via Warden.

ğŸ” Deep explanation

Uses cookies â†’ session â†’ Warden

Internally:

