8ï¸âƒ£ What happens when a user logs in?
âœ… Short answer

Devise authenticates credentials, stores user in session, and makes current_user available.

ğŸ” Deep explanation (step-by-step)

User submits login form

Devise controller receives params

Warden verifies credentials

Password compared via bcrypt

User ID stored in session

9ï¸âƒ£ What is rememberable?
âœ… Short answer

It allows users to stay logged in using cookies even after session expiry.

ğŸ” Deep explanation

Generates a remember token

Stores hashed token in DB

Stores signed cookie in browser

Re-authenticates user automatically

ğŸ”Ÿ Difference between session and remember me?
âœ… Short answer

Session is short-lived; remember me is persistent using cookies.

ğŸ” Deep explanation
Session	Remember Me
Stored in server session	Stored in browser cookie
Cleared on browser close	Persists for weeks
Faster	More secure tokens
